Docs.summary: Provides an immutable, read-only dictionary optimized for fast lookup and enumeration.
Docs.remarks: is immutable and is optimized for situations where a dictionary is created infrequently but is used frequently at run time. It has a relatively high cost to create but provides excellent lookup performance. Thus, it is ideal for cases where a dictionary is created once, potentially at the startup of an application, and is used throughout the remainder of the life of the application. should only be initialized with trusted keys, as the details of the keys impacts construction time.
